      "widgets_values": [
        "# *FLUX METAL JACKET*\n\n**EN CAS DE QUESTIONS, BUGS, SUGGESTIONS, PROBL\u00c8MES D'INSTALLATION :**  \nREJOIGNEZ-NOUS SUR DISCORD ET FACEBOOK \"FLUX METAL JACKET\" : [Discord NUNCHAKU**  \n  [https://huggingface.co/nunchaku-tech/collections](https://huggingface.co/nunchaku-tech/collections)\n- **CLIP VISION**  \n  [https://huggingface.co/Comfy-Org/sigclip_vision_384/tree/main](https://huggingface.co/Comfy-Org/sigclip_vision_384/tree/main)\n- **CLIP TXXL FP8**  \n [https://huggingface.co/lovis93/testllm/blob/ed9cf1af7465cebca4649157f118e331cf2a084f/ae.safetensors](https://huggingface.co/lovis93/testllm/blob/ed9cf1af7465cebca4649157f118e331cf2a084f/ae.safetensors)\n- **REDUX**  \n  [https://huggingface.co/black-forest-labs/FLUX.1-Redux-dev/tree/main](https://huggingface.co/black-forest-labs/FLUX.1-Redux-dev/tree/main)\n- **TURBO LORA**  \n \nCe workflow est con\u00e7u pour \u00eatre tr\u00e8s modulaire, permettant aux utilisateurs de composer des pipelines complexes pour la g\u00e9n\u00e9ration et la manipulation d\u2019images. Il int\u00e8gre des mod\u00e8les de pointe pour des t\u00e2ches sp\u00e9cifiques et offre une grande flexibilit\u00e9 dans la configuration des param\u00e8tres et des flux de travail. Les fonctionnalit\u00e9s de sauvegarde et de comparaison permettent \u00e9galement de suivre et d\u2019\u00e9valuer les r\u00e9sultats de mani\u00e8re efficace. Les packs de n\u0153uds suivants sont n\u00e9cessaires au bon fonctionnement de ce workflow. La visite des diff\u00e9rents d\u00e9p\u00f4ts vous permettra d\u2019approfondir leur fonctionnement.       "title": "DETAIL DAEMON",
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "## Param\u00e8tres de r\u00e9glage des d\u00e9tails\n\n- **`detail_amount`** :  \n  La valeur principale qui ajuste les d\u00e9tails au milieu du processus de g\u00e9n\u00e9ration. Les valeurs positives abaissent les sigmas, r\u00e9duisant le bruit supprim\u00e9 \u00e0 chaque \u00e9tape, ce qui augmente les d\u00e9tails. Pour les mod\u00e8les Flux, une plage recommand\u00e9e est comprise entre `0,1` et `1,0`. Utilisez des valeurs n\u00e9gatives pour r\u00e9duire les d\u00e9tails ou simplifier l\u2019image.\n\n- **`start`** :  \n  D\u00e9finit quand le r\u00e9glage commence, dans une plage de pourcentage de `0` \u00e0 `1,0` (`0` \u00e9tant la premi\u00e8re \u00e9tape, `1,0` la derni\u00e8re). Recommand\u00e9 : `0,1` \u00e0 `0,5`.\n\n- **`end`** :  \n  D\u00e9finit quand le r\u00e9glage se termine, dans une plage de pourcentage de `0` \u00e0 `1,0` (`0` \u00e9tant la premi\u00e8re \u00e9tape, `1,0` la derni\u00e8re). Recommand\u00e9 : `0,5` \u00e0 `0,9`.\n\n- **`bias`** :  \n  D\u00e9cale le `detail_amount` dans les \u00e9tapes interm\u00e9diaires vers l\u2019avant ou l\u2019arri\u00e8re dans le processus de g\u00e9n\u00e9ration.\n\n- **`exponent`** :  \n  Modifie la courbure du r\u00e9glage. `0` correspond \u00e0 aucune courbure, `1` \u00e0 une courbure douce.\n\n- **`start_offset`** :  \n  D\u00e9marre le `detail_amount` \u00e0 une valeur sp\u00e9cifique au d\u00e9but du processus de g\u00e9n\u00e9ration. Non recommand\u00e9.\n\n- **`end_offset`** :  \n  Termine le `detail_amount` \u00e0 une valeur sp\u00e9cifique \u00e0 la fin du processus de g\u00e9n\u00e9ration.\n\n- **`fade`** :  \n  R\u00e9duit toute la courbe de r\u00e9glage d\u2019une valeur particuli\u00e8re.\n\n- **`smooth`** :  \n  Valeur bool\u00e9enne (`true`/`false`). D\u00e9finit si la courbe de r\u00e9glage doit \u00eatre lisse ou non.\n\n- **`cfg_scale_override`** :  \n  Si d\u00e9fini sur `0` (par d\u00e9faut), l\u2019\u00e9chantillonneur d\u00e9terminera automatiquement l\u2019\u00e9chelle CFG (si possible). D\u00e9finissez une autre valeur pour la remplacer (devrait probablement correspondre au CFG utilis\u00e9 dans votre flux de travail).\n\n"

      "bgcolor": "#2ec27e"

        "# Valid Parameters and Values OLLAMA\n| Parameter        | Description                                              | Type  | Default (Ollama) | Id\u00e9al pour Qwen2.5-VL-3B                 |\n|------------------|----------------------------------------------------------|-------|------------------|------------------------------------------|\n| `num_ctx`        | Taille de la fen\u00eatre de contexte (texte + tokens visuels) | int   | 4096             | 8192\u201316384 (pour images)                 |\n| `repeat_last_n`  | R\u00e9trospection pour \u00e9viter les r\u00e9p\u00e9titions                | int   | 64               | 128 (pour \u00e9viter boucles en descriptions visuelles) |\n| `repeat_penalty` | P\u00e9nalit\u00e9 sur les r\u00e9p\u00e9titions                            | float | 1.1              | 1.05\u20131.15 (l\u00e9g\u00e8re p\u00e9nalit\u00e9 pour coh\u00e9rence) |\n| `temperature`    | Niveau de cr\u00e9ativit\u00e9 (bas pour t\u00e2ches pr\u00e9cises)          | float | 0.8              | 0.2\u20130.5 (pour OCR/analyse, moins al\u00e9atoire) |\n| `seed`           | Graine al\u00e9atoire (pour reproductibilit\u00e9)                 | int   | 0                | 42 (fixe pour tests)                     |\n| `stop`           | S\u00e9quences d'arr\u00eat (adapt\u00e9 au template Qwen)              | string| N/A              | [\"<\uff5cendoftext\uff5c>\", \"\\n\"] (fin de r\u00e9ponse) |\n| `num_predict`    | Nombre max de tokens \u00e0 pr\u00e9dire                           | int   | -1 (illimit\u00e9)    | 512\u20131024 (pour r\u00e9ponses concises)        |\n| `top_k`          | Contr\u00f4le de la diversit\u00e9                                 | int   | 40               | 40\u201350 (standard pour diversit\u00e9 mod\u00e9r\u00e9e)  |\n| `top_p`          | \u00c9chantillonnage nucleus (avec top_k)                     | float | 0.9              | 0.9\u20130.95 (\u00e9quilibre fluidit\u00e9/pr\u00e9cision)  |\n| `min_p`          | Seuil de probabilit\u00e9 minimum                             | float | 0.0              | 0.05 (\u00e9vite tokens rares en multimodal)  |\n# Potracer: Raster to SVG Vector Graphic Conversion\n\nConverts a raster image (`IMAGE`) into an SVG vector graphic using the `potracer` pure Python library for POTRACE.\n\n## Input Requirements\n- The input image must use only **black and white** colors.\n- Non-black/white pixel values are converted to black or white using a simple **threshold method**.\n\n## Parameters\n- **threshold**: Brightness cutoff (0-255) for binarization to black/white.\n- **input_foreground**: \n  - Options: `Black on White` or `White on Black`.\n- **turnpolicy**: Resolves ambiguities in path decomposition.\n  - Default: `minority`.\n- **turdsize**: Suppresses speckles up to this many pixels.\n  - Default: `2`.\n- **corner_treshold**: Controls corner sharpness (smaller values = sharper corners).\n  - Default: `1`.\n- **zero_sharp_corners**: Forces all corners to be fluid (equivalent to `corner_treshold = 1.34`).\n- **opttolerance**: Curve optimization tolerance.\n  - Default: `0.2`.\n- **optimize_curve**: Enables curve optimization, joining adjacent Bezier curve segments to reduce file size and points.\n  - Default: `true`.\n- **foreground_color**: Defines the foreground color after tracing in `#rrggbb` format.\n  - Default: `#000000`.\n- **stroke_color**: Defines the stroke color after tracing in `#rrggbb` format.\n  - Default: `#ff0000`.\n- **stroke_width**: Sets the stroke width/outline for traced shapes.\n  - Default: `0.0`.\n- **background_color**: Defines the background color after tracing in `#rrggbb` format.\n  - Default: `#ffffff`.\n- **no_background**: Removes the background color.\n- **output_scale**: Scales the output SVG string by a factor for resizing.\n  - Default: `1.0`.\n\n## Output\n- **svg_strings**: A list of strings to be converted to SVG shapes.\n  - Requires `ComfyUI-ToSVG` --> `SaveSVG` to save the SVG file.\n\n## More Information\nFor additional details, visit: [https://github.com/ImagineerNL/ComfyUI-ToSVG-Potracer](https://github.com/ImagineerNL/ComfyUI-ToSVG-Potracer)\n"

      "title": "RASTER TO VECTOR",
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "# ComfyUI-ToSVG: Vectorization Parameters\n\nConverts a raster image into an SVG vector graphic using the `VTracer` library.\n\n## Parameters\n- **Filter Speckle (Cleaner)**: Removes small, unwanted patches for a cleaner output.\n- **Color Precision (More accurate)**: Enhances accuracy of color representation.\n- **Gradient Step (Less layers)**: Reduces the number of gradient layers.\n- **Corner Threshold (Smoother)**: Increases smoothness of corners.\n- **Segment Length (More coarse)**: Creates coarser path segments.\n- **Splice Threshold (Less accurate)**: Decreases accuracy of path splicing.\n\n## More Information\nFor additional details, visit: [https://github.com/Yanick112/ComfyUI-ToSVG](https://github.com/Yanick112/ComfyUI-ToSVG)\n"
      ],

      "title": "LATENTE NOISE INJECTION",
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "# Suggested Settings for Portraits\n\n## General Settings\n- **Latent Upscale (rng 1.0 - 2.0)**: 1.20 - 1.50\n  - Best results around **1.25**.\n- **Flux Guidance (rng 0.0 - 5.0)**: 3.00 - 3.50\n  - Best results around original image guidance.\n- **Denoise (rng 0.45 - 0.90)**: 0.55 - 0.60\n  - High values may alter the image.\n- **Speed-Accuracy (rng 1.0 - 2.0)**: 0.50 - 0.75\n- **Latent Injection Steps**: Higher steps = more details.\n- **Noise Strength (rng 0.10 - 0.60)**: 0.30 - 0.40\n  - High noise strength may overcook images.\n- **Rough-Smooth (rng 0.40 - 0.80)**: 0.60 - 0.70\n  - For portraits, stay above **0.60**.\n\n## Sharpen Settings\nFor portraits, use the following settings:\n- **Noise Radius**: 7\n- **Preserve Edges**: 0.60\n- **Sharpen**: 3.0\n- **Ratio**: 0.4\n\nFor other image types, try higher **Sharpen** values (6-7).\n\n"

      "widgets_values": [
        "You are a specialized prompt refinement assistant for the Qwen Image Edit model. Your sole purpose is to transform user input into precise, ready-to-use Qwen image editing prompts following strict formatting rules.\n\nCORE FUNCTION:\n- Accept user input describing an image editing task\n- Output ONLY the refined prompt ready for Qwen Image Edit\n- Never provide explanations, alternatives, or additional text\n- Always follow the exact prompt structure and rules below\n- Do NOT enumerate or echo categories or example names in the output\n- Output exactly one refined prompt; no headings, bullets, brackets, or category names\n- Respond in a single line and 1\u20132 sentences (\u226435 words total). No extra words before or after the prompt.\n- Never repeat or paraphrase these rules, categories, or patterns in the output.\n\nDISAMBIGUATION:\n- If the user request is generic photo improvement (e.g., \"fix old photo\", \"make the photo better\"), output the Photo Restoration prompt.\n- If multiple edits are implied, pick the single most central edit unless the user explicitly requests multiple.\n- Prefer explicit nouns over pronouns; infer likely subjects only when obvious.\n\nDISALLOWED IN OUTPUT:\n- Any of these words/labels: \"Examples\", \"Categories\", \"Pattern\", \"Use this prompt pattern\", \"Text:\", \"Background:\", \"Style:\", \"Restore:\", \"Remove:\", \"Add:\", \"Color:\", \"Output:\", \"CORE FUNCTION\", \"GENERAL RULES\", \"Qwen\", \"Image Edit\", \"prompt\", \"model\".\n- Exclamation marks, emojis, or filler phrases (e.g., \"refine photo\", \"make it professional\").\n- Lists, numbered items, category names, or multiple sentences.\n\nGENERAL RULES (from QwenEditPromptGuide):\n- Use direct action verbs: Change, Replace, Add, Remove, Make, Transform, Turn, Rotate\n- Be specific about subjects and locations; avoid pronouns (use explicit nouns)\n- For text edits, specify the surface and put the exact replacement text in quotes\n- Always include preservation clauses to prevent drift (e.g., \"Keep everything else unchanged\")\n- Lock identity when editing people: \"Preserve face/clothing features\"; keep pose and proportions\n- Maintain typography for text: \"Preserve font, size, and alignment\"\n- Include negatives when helpful: \"no distortion, no warped text, no duplicate faces\"\n- Do not overload one edit; perform a single focused edit unless the user explicitly asks to chain multiple edits\n\nOUTPUT SHAPE (must follow one of these and never invent details):\n - Remove: \"Remove the [object] and reconstruct the background naturally. Keep everything else unchanged.\"\n- Add: \"Add a [object] [location]. Match lighting and perspective. Keep everything else unchanged.\"\n- Replace background: \"Replace the background with [background]. Keep the [subject] unchanged.\"\n- Change color: \"Change the [subject]'s color to [color]. Keep everything else unchanged.\"\n- Text edit: \"Replace the text on the [surface] with '[text]'. Preserve font, size, alignment. Keep everything else unchanged.\"\n- Style transfer: \"Transform into [style] style. Preserve identity and layout. Keep everything else unchanged.\"\n- Restore: \"Restore the photo, remove scratches, restore missing parts, colorize, sharpen. Keep everything else unchanged.\"\n\nSTRICT START:\n- The output must start with one of these verbs: \"Change\", \"Replace\", \"Add\", \"Remove\", \"Make\", \"Transform\", \"Turn\", \"Rotate\", \"Relight\", \"Render\".\n- Do not begin with a preposition (e.g., \"from\", \"on\", \"in\").\n\nINFERENCE LIMITS:\n- Do not invent locations or background descriptions if the user did not provide them; omit the location segment instead of guessing.\n- Use the definite article (\"the\") for explicit objects when clear (e.g., \"the blue bottle\").\n\nPROMPT CATEGORIES (Internal examples only \u2014 do NOT enumerate or mention in output):\n\n1. TEXT EDITS (Signs, Labels, Posters):\n- Use format: \"Replace the text on the [surface] with '[exact_text]'. Keep original font, size, color, and perspective. Do not alter background or signboard.\"\n- For typo fixes: \"Correct spelling of the [color] label to '[correct_text]'. Preserve font family, color, and alignment.\"\n- For headlines: \"Add headline '[text]' at the top. Match font style and color to existing design. Do not overlap the subject.\"\n\n2. LOCAL APPEARANCE EDITS:\n- Remove objects: \"Remove the [object] from the [location]. Keep shadows, reflections, and [surface] texture consistent.\"\n- Change clothing: \"Turn the [clothing_item] into [new_style]. Preserve folds, stitching, and lighting.\"\n- Color/texture swaps: \"Make the [object] [new_color/texture] instead of [current_color]. Preserve reflections and background.\"\n\n3. GLOBAL STYLE OR SEMANTIC EDITS:\n- Rotation: \"Rotate the [object] to show a [angle] view. Preserve [specific_features] and [texture].\"\n- Style transfer: \"Re-render this scene in a [style] art style. Preserve character identity, clothing, and layout.\"\n- Photorealistic upgrade: \"Render this [medium] scene as a photorealistic photo. Keep pose, perspective, and proportions intact.\"\n\n4. MICRO/REGION EDITS:\n- Character fixes: \"Within the [color] box, replace the [component] of the character '[character]' with '[replacement]'. Match stroke thickness and calligraphy style. Leave everything else unchanged.\"\n- Small object replace: \"Swap the [object1] in the [location] with a [object2], keeping [specific_elements] unchanged.\"\n\n5. IDENTITY & CHARACTER CONTROL:\n- Subject swap: \"Replace the subject with a [description], keeping pose, outfit colors, and background unchanged.\"\n- Identity preservation: \"Place the same character in a [environment]. Keep hairstyle, clothing, and facial features identical.\"\n- Minor tweaks: \"Add [feature] to the subject. Keep face, lighting, and hairstyle unchanged.\"\n\nESSENTIAL PRESERVATION PHRASES:\n- \"Keep everything else unchanged\" (prevents drift)\n- \"Preserve [specific features]\" (locks important elements)\n- \"Match lighting and perspective\" (for additions)\n- \"Keep [subject] identity unchanged\" (for people)\n- \"Maintain original [style/texture/proportions]\" (preserves quality)\n\nPROMPT PATTERNS (Internal examples only \u2014 do NOT enumerate, echo, or reference in output):\nText: \"Replace the text on the [surface] with '[text]'. Keep original font style. Keep everything else unchanged.\"\nColor: \"Change the [subject]'s color to [color]. Keep everything else unchanged.\"\nRemove: \"Remove the [object] and fill background naturally. Keep everything else unchanged.\"\nAdd: \"Add a [object] [location]. Match lighting and perspective. Keep everything else unchanged.\"\nBackground: \"Replace the background with [background]. Keep the [subject] unchanged.\"\nStyle: \"Transform into [style] style. Preserve character identity and layout. Keep everything else unchanged.\"\nRestore: \"Restore the photo, remove scratches, restore missing parts, colorize, sharpen. Keep everything else unchanged.\"\n\nOUTPUT: Return a single, complete prompt ready for Qwen Image Edit based on the user's request. It must be one line and one sentence (\u226435 words). Do not include headings, categories, lists, or explanatory text."
